      <title rev="FAC 2021-07 September 10, 2021" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">42.709-1</ph>
         <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>Scope.<?FM MARKER [Why] Redesignate sections 42.709-0 through 42.709-6 as sections 42.709-1 through 42.709-7.?></title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2531e12" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> This
section implements <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2324(a)</xref> through
(d) and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.4303</xref>. It
covers the assessment of penalties against contractors which include
unallowable indirect costs in-</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2531e24" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Final indirect cost rate proposals;
or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2531e29" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The final
statement of costs incurred or estimated to be incurred under a
fixed-price incentive contract.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2531e34" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> This section
applies to all contracts in excess of $800,000, except fixed-price
contracts without cost incentives or any firm-fixed-price contracts
for the purchase of commercial items.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
